name: Ernesto G. Aguilar
text: The best pizza hut pizza I've had in a while. I live in Ventura and I usually don't go to the pizza hut there because it's not that good. I work here in Newbury and I wasn't expecting much to be completely honest. However when I opened the box I was completely surprised. The pizza looked fluffy and was really good.

name: Lorenzo Gonzalez
text: Fast, convenient, and sinfully delicious. Sure, the sausage "crumbles" look suspiciously similar to milk-soaked dry cat food (as pointed out by my vegetarian and therefore totally biased wife). But do I care? Nope. Taste great to me. Plus it was ready on time and the guy running the joint was friendly and cool.

name: Tavi Scratch
text: Pretty nice establishment, I like the interior design and the food was prepared in a quick Manor. If I had any issues it would be the noise the door made when I stood near it, but it's easily avoided if you don't stand so close to it so I didn't have too much of an issue there. All in all it's a great place and I would come again.
